# Subjects' Connection

# First Episode
										Bir cümle bitirilene kadar, bu kısım kendini arka arkaya kopyalayabilir.
						modal verb			------------------------------------------------------------------------------
		(noun/pronoun)			verb + verb (gerund/infinitive)				(noun/pronoun)
		subject				verb (tenses)			preposition		object 		/	adjective	/	adverb		conjunction
🟣		🔴 ---------------------------- 🔴 ---------------------------- 🔵 ------------------- 🔵 ----------------------------------------------------		🟣
													
																					
						modal verb - yardımcı fiil												conjunction - bağlaç (iki cümleyi bağlar)
		   noun - isim			gerund (V + Ving)											adverb - zarf (fiili niteler)
		pronoun - zamir			infinitive (V to V)								adjective - sıfat (ismi niteler)
		subject - özne (eylemi yapan)	verb - fiil, eylem		preposition - edat	object - nesne (eyleme maruz kalan)
										(iki kelimeyi bağlar)





# Second Episode

										ACTIVE VOICE
										(Etken Çatı)
		------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

		▫️▫️▫️						▫️▫️▫️					▫️▫️▫️
		past perfect continuous				past continuous (-iyordu)		present perfect continuous
		#						#					#						 (-iyor..)
Tenses		past perfect (-mış,-miş)			past simple (-dı,-di)			present perfect (-dı,-di)		present continuous ----------|---> be going to
		🔴～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～ 🔴 ----------------------------------- 🔴～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～～ 🔵 - - - - - - - - - -> FUTURE (-acak, -ecek)
		1. Verb						2. Verb										      	  |------> will

		|						|					|					|
		|	PERFECT					|	PAST				|	PRESENT				|
Modals		|	MODALS					|	MODALS				|	MODALS				|
		|	could  have V3				|	could  V1			|	can 	V1			|
		|	would  have V3				|	would  V1			|	will 	V1 (future simple)	|
		|	might  have V3				|	might  V1			|	may	V1			|
		|	should have V3				|	should V1			|	shall	V1			|			
		|	must   have V3				|					|	must	V1			|
		|						|					|					|
		|						|					|					|

Conditionals	type 3 (Impossible)				type 2 (Less Possible)			type 1 (Possible)			type 0 (Certain)
                If + Past Perfect / 				If + Past Simple /			If + Present Time, Present Modal	If + Present Simple, Present Simple
		     Past Perfect Continuous, perfect modal	     Past Continuous, Past Modal		










